Defendant David A Brown in court with attorney Michael L. Chernin.  Jayne Davis Dewire appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Neither party has any correction to the PSI.  Court notes incorrect case number on Page 19.
State makes sentencing recommendation.  Defense makes sentencing recommendation.  Defendant makes statement.  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED SENTENCE of: 

5 YEARS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - 62 days).  Defendant remanded to custody forthwith.  
  -  2 YEAR(S) OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  3 YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.'s; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed;
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions;
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling;

RESTITUTION:  $925.00 in buy money to Waukesha Metro Drug Unit (apply cash bail; balance to be refunded to poster;

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (apply cash bail; balance to be refunded to poster)

DNA SURCHARGE:   $250.00 (apply cash bail; balance to be refunded to poster)
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.

Defendant is eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
